{
  "stem": "8892.2",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the gendarme noticed this, because one was always walking behind a wagon and one was sitting who was handling the horses, you know, and noticed that.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he gave him with his pistol, with his shotgun, a clop on his head that I thought he was going to die right there and faint.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he just fell down, and then he is on the ground.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And when my father saw this, I don't think-- I don't even know what was the reaction.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I think we all just screamed or cried.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then we were loading up, but they started at one end of the town, and then that's how they went.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we were loading up, and my brother stayed, of course, behind and that was the last thing we knew of him.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That's it.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then we went to Satoraljaujhely, which was a big Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's where they made the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What happened there, that all the Jews who used to live-- wasn't a ghetto, but let's say confined more to 10 blocks of Jewish people, they emptied it.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They emptied their furniture.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They confiscated everything, and they took that 10 blocks or so and more like-- it wasn't a desirable area, more towards the gypsies where they would be end of the town, outskirts of the town, and emptied that, and they put like four or five families to one house.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's how a ghetto was.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it wasn't barracks or anything.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a regular building, regular thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were somehow lucky that we actually wind up in the same building where our cousin lived in Satoraljaujhely.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when we went there-- they were younger than my parents-- they had beautiful furniture.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
